item.title: Making A Jar File [PI]
item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

This is more of a client help thread.

I am not entirely sure how the cachedownloader class works, but I am guessing all it does is connect to the url in its path and then downloads the cache that way. So no you would still need to jar the entire client and then have the web page load the jar, then you would run that client which would call the methods with in the class, which would download the cache.
